# Memory logging

`.memory/project.db` is the **live source of truth** (highest precedence). Keep it current — it is how state survives across sessions.

## Session start
```bash
python3 .memory/log.py session start
python3 .memory/log.py context dump      # surface open tasks + last next_step
```

## During the session
```bash
# record a non-trivial decision (alternatives + consequences matter)
python3 .memory/log.py decision add --title "..." --context "..." \
  --decision "..." --rationale "..." --alternatives "..." --consequences "..."

# track task status as you move
python3 .memory/log.py task update --id TASK-XXX --status in_progress|done
```

## Session end
```bash
python3 .memory/log.py session end --summary "..." --next_step "..."
```

Log a decision whenever you make a real design choice, and update task status when you start or finish a unit of work — don't leave the DB behind the actual state.
